      <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 6h16M4 12h16M4 18h16" stroke="#94a3b8" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
      <span>CLINICIAN</span>
      <span class="muted">/</span>
      <span class="muted">Preguntas basadas en “General histology”</span>
    </div>

    <div class="panel" role="region" aria-labelledby="qtitle">
      <div class="question">
        <h2 id="qtitle">Clinical question</h2>
        <p> A 31-year-old woman comes to the emergency department because of a 4-week history of worsening headache, nausea, and vomiting. The headache is worse at night. Fundoscopic examination shows swelling of the optic discs. A CT scan of the brain shows a heterogeneous, hyperintense, intraventricular mass. The patient undergoes surgical excision of the mass. Pathologic examination of the surgical specimen confirms that the tumor is of <em>neuronal origin</em>. The cells in this specimen are most likely to stain positive for which of the following immunohistochemical markers?</p>
      </div>

      <form class="options" id="opts">
        <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="ans" value="A"><code>A</code><span>S-100</span></label>
        <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="ans" value="B"><code>B</code><span>Desmin</span></label>
        <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="ans" value="C"><code>C</code><span>Synaptophysin</span></label>
        <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="ans" value="D"><code>D</code><span>Glial fibrillary acidic protein (GFAP)</span></label>
        <label class="opt"><input type="radio" name="ans" value="E"><code>E</code><span>Cytokeratin</span></label>
      </form>

      <div class="btns">
        <span class="muted">Selecciona una opción y luego “Mostrar respuesta”.</span>
        <div>
          <button id="reveal">Mostrar respuesta</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="answer" id="answer">
        <p><strong>Respuesta correcta: C — Synaptophysin.</strong></p>
        <p>Es un marcador neuronal (vesículas presinápticas) positivo en tumores de origen <em>neuronal</em> como neurocitomas/gangliogliomas. <br/>
        <span class="note">S-100 y GFAP suelen asociarse a estirpe glial; desmina a músculo; citoqueratinas a epitelio.</span></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="source">Inspirado en una tarjeta de práctica de AMBOSS. Esta página es solo con fines educativos.</p>
  </div>

  <script>
    const btn = document.getElementById('reveal');
    const box = document.getElementById('answer');
    btn.addEventListener('click', function (e){
      e.preventDefault();
      box.classList.add('show');
      btn.setAttribute('disabled', 'disabled');
      btn.textContent = 'Respuesta mostrada';
    });
  </script>
